far as practical.Top 4 Senior Officers, shall be rotated on same type of vessels and maintain continuity by assigning similar type of vessels under thesame Charterer after completion of senior officers leave period.All other officers and ratings shall as far as practical be rotated on same type of vessel and if no suitable vacancies available at thetime of reporting, then they shall be assigned to other vessels which are under our management.4.24SAFE MANNING AND ADDITIONAL MAN POWERIt is Company Policy that vessels are appropriately manned in order to encompass all aspects of maintaining safe operation on boardin accordance with the Principles of minimum safe manning, adopted by the Organization by Resolution A. 1047(27). taking intoaccount the trade and operational requirements of the vessel.The Company shall ensure compliance by supplying additional manpower on board as required.4.25PROMOTION PROCEDURECompany provides career development for junior officers and General Manager.5PURCHASING AND MANAGEMENT OF SUPPLIERS5.1PURCHASING POLICYThe Company believes that the basis for correct purchasing is dependent upon regular and accurate stock taking. Maintaining excessstocks on board is poor economy and must be avoided.Efficient purchasing can be defined as giving maximum service to the ship at minimum expense to the owner. The parameters for thiscan be stated as correct quantity, quality, price and delivery time. To achieve this requires intimate coordination between the vesselstaff and the office.Ordering/ purchasing of stores or spares is normally to be made through the PHOENIX system. Exception to this being purchases ofprovisions or urgent store requirement for which prior approval of the office has been sought.Master has the authority to procure stores or spares without prior sanction from the company in case of emergencies involving shipsseaworthiness, safety or pollution risks.
